  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Employement of Syrian refugees in Turkey: Phase 4</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Employment of Syrian refugees at Dutch companies in Turkey is a project which goes beyond humanitarian aid and aims to provide a solid future for Syrian refugees living in Turkey. In the year 2017 a pilot started to establish an infrastructure and approach to help Syrian refugees to a job, preferably with Dutch companies in Turkey. A total of 220 placements were achieved. Based on this pilot the activities were continued in 2018 achieving 2000 placements and at least as many training activities. Furthermore the infrastructure to support the activities in Turkey will be extended through new branches in Izmir and Bursa besides the main office in Istanbul. The project is made possible with the financial support of the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs</narrative>
  </description>
